  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zimbabwe Cash Preparedness</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Summary ECHO 2018 &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x201C; 2020 :&#xC2;&#xA0; Resilience through Disaster Response Management; Multipurpose Cash Preparedness and Comprehensive School Safety. Working with the Finnish Red Cross, and WFP - Based in Harare and Mangwe district1) Strengthened capacities to use multi-purpose cash transfer as a mean of humanitarian aid delivery mechanism2) Children and youth, and their home communities, are more resilient to disasters and have safer learning environments through the enhanced contribution of the Red Cross to the Comprehensive School Safety Framework in Zimbabwe.3)Distribution of first aid, basic safety and student care equipment to schools as well as distribution of IEC materials for youth and children.
Summary ECHO 2020 &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x201C; 2021 Following on a lot of the work of ECHO 2018, ECHO 2020 sees the following two results1) Safe schools -ZRCS will in this Action through its strong partnership with the DCP and MoPSE work on expanding the reach of its school safety interventions and promote the standardization of processes and tools as part of DCP&#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2122;s national school safety guidelines.2) Cash Preparedness and Shock Responsive Social Protection Systems - To enable ZRCS to deliver appropriate assistance using CTP to people in a timely and efficient manner, the CTP within ZRCS is to be strengthened and standardized, with more staff trained (on design, assessment, ZRCS is to be strengthened and standardized, with more staff trained (on design, assessment, implementation, finance, etc.), and learnings disseminated and used for improvement
&#xC2;&#xA0;
Location: Zimbabwe &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x201C; Harare and Mangwe districtBens: Direct beneficiaries of the entire programme - 23,060 peopleDonor: ECHO and General fundsPNSs: Finnish Red Cross</narrative>
  </description>
